{"lemma":"اِبْنٌ","slug":"اِبْنٌ","root":"ب.ن.#","root_slug":"ب-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"اِبْنٌ","root":"بني","pos":"N","occurrence_count":63},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n100","n3342","n3368"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A7%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to eulogize, to pay homage to a dead person, to commemorate the times of"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be on the tracks of, to follow the traces of","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to watch, to observe, to wait for","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stick, to stay, to remain","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"يَا كَرَوَانًا ضُكَّ فَأَكْبَأَنَّا\nفَشَنَّ بِٱلسَلْخِ فَلَمَّا شَنَّا … بَلَّ ٱلذُنَابَى عَبَسًا مُبِنَّا","english":"You thick-knee! Which when bumped will clew and toss dung and having hurled … moistens the tail with sticky soil!"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of إِبَّان (ʔibbān, “time”).\n\nDenominal verb of بَنَّة (banna, “odour in particular from lodging-places due to cattle”), or a previous meaning “ground” of بُنّ (bunn), Omani Arabic بُون (būn, “origin, root”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n100","headword_ar":"اِبْنٌ","root":"Abn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bny","text_ar":"بني"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3342","headword_ar":"اِبْنٌ","root":"bnw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", held by some to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawN","text_ar":"بَنَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3368","headword_ar":"اِبْنٌ","root":"bnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A son;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K;) because he is the father's building, made to be so by God; (Er-Rághib, TA;) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a son's son;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a descendant more remote;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) is with a conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[when not immediately preceded by a quiescence, written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonN","text_ar":"ا@بْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Zj, T, M;) [and when immediately preceded by the proper name of a man and immediately followed by the proper name of his parent, written without the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodu bonu EamorKw","text_ar":"زَيْدُ بْنُ عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd the son of 'Amr"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in which case it should also be observed that the former proper name is without tenween); unless the words compose a proposition, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN A@bonu EamorKw","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ ا@بْنُ عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is the son of 'Amr;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or in the case of an interrogation, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo zayodN A@bonu EamorKw","text_ar":"هَلْ زَيْدٌ ا@بْنُ عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is Zeyd the son of 'Amr?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the pl. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuwna","text_ar":"بَنُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, Msb) in the nom. case, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniyna","text_ar":"بَنِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the accus. and gen.; (Mgh;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) which is a pl. of pauc.: (Msb:) [and hence it is argued that] the sing. is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the final radical letter elided and the conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed; (M;) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaYN","text_ar":"بَنَىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as we judge, because [the aor.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaboniY","text_ar":"يَبْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabonuw","text_ar":"يَبْنُو"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawN","text_ar":"بَنَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) with two fet-hahs, because it has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuwna","text_ar":"بَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a pl., and the perfect pl. does not admit of change [in its vowels beyond that which is here made in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuwna","text_ar":"بَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawuwna","text_ar":"بَنَوُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) and because it has for a pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalN","text_ar":"جَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaAlN","text_ar":"اَجْمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and the elided letter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, T, S,) as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abN","text_ar":"اَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axN","text_ar":"اَخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more commonly elided than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Akh, T;) or because the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axN","text_ar":"اَخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxotN","text_ar":"اُخْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for we do not see this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"] affixed in the fem. except when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is elided in the masc., as is shown by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axawaAtN","text_ar":"اَخَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hanawaAtN","text_ar":"هَنَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bunuw~apN","text_ar":"بُنُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not a decisive proof that the last radical is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", for a reason stated above in the explanation of it: (T:) or, as some say, it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binowN","text_ar":"بِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimolN","text_ar":"حِمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and a change [of a vowel] in a case of this kind is rare: (Msb:) [but J says,] it may not be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolN","text_ar":"فُعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuwna","text_ar":"بَنُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", for a pl.; nor of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this has [generally] for its [broken] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEulN","text_ar":"اَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) Zj says that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binoYN","text_ar":"بِنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binowN","text_ar":"بِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or it may be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banFA","text_ar":"بَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; that it is app. the last accord. to those who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuwn","text_ar":"بَنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"favours its being of the latter; but that it may be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"changed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolN","text_ar":"فُعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxotN","text_ar":"اُخْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) Beside the pls. mentioned above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a quasi-pl. n., namely ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaY","text_ar":"اَبْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the same measure as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomaY","text_ar":"اَعْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, TA; *) a sing. denoting the pl.: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has for pls."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaA='N","text_ar":"اَبْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaY","text_ar":"اَبْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Lh mentions the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i A^abonaA A^abonaAy^ihimo","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ اَبْنَا اَبْنَايِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abonaY AbnAy^hm","text_ar":"اَبْنَى ابنايهم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are the sons of their sons."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) Sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is affixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that it becomes ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonumN","text_ar":"اِبْنُمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonamN","text_ar":"اِبْنَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"at the beginning of a sentence, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonumN","text_ar":"ا@بْنُمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bunamN","text_ar":"ا@بُنَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in other cases]: the word is then doubly declinable [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimoruw^N","text_ar":"اِمْرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@moruA^N","text_ar":"ا@مْرُاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A@bonumN","text_ar":"هٰذَا ا@بْنُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a son"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu A@bonamFA","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ ا@بْنَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw a son"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mararotu biA@bonimK","text_ar":"مَرَرْتُ بِا@بْنِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed by a son"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; making the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"similarly declinable to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with kesr in every case [when the word commences a sentence, whether you make the word doubly declinable or not]: (AHeyth, * S:) [for] some make it singly declinable, leaving the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"with fet-h in every case [as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^N","text_ar":"اِمْرَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@moraA^N","text_ar":"ا@مْرَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A@bonamuka","text_ar":"هٰذَا ا@بْنَمُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is thy son"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu A@bonamaka","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ ا@بْنَمَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw thy son"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mararotu biA@bonamika","text_ar":"مَرَرْتُ بِا@بْنَمِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed by thy son"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AHeyth, TA.) Hassán says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waladonaA baniY AlEanoqaA='i waA@bonaYo muHar~iqK\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      faA^akorimo binaA xaAlFA waA^akorimo binaA A@bonamaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We begot the sons of El-'Ankà, and the two sons of Moharrik; and how generous are we as a maternal uncle! and how generous are we as a son!"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K, *) i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaA","text_ar":"ا@بْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative, and the hemzeh [or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is that of conjunction. (K.) And Ru-beh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      fahoYa tunaAdiY biA^abiY waA@boniymaA \n                      \n                     \n                        bukaA='a $akolaY faqadato HamiymaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As the weeping of a bereft woman, who has lost a relation, therefore she calls out, With my father"},{"kind":"text","text":"would I ransom thee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a son"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonimaA","text_ar":"ا@بْنِمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonapN","text_ar":"اِبْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonapN","text_ar":"ا@بْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[with the conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"when not commencing a sentence] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A daughter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any female descendant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K:) accord. to Sb, (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonapN","text_ar":"اِبْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by affixing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but not so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for this is formed by affixing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a letter of quasi-coordination, and then substituting for it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) [but if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"be substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", it seems more probable that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the final radical:] or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [Mtr says,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for the final radical: (Mgh:) accord. to Ks, it is originally with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"], because it has a fem. meaning: (IAar, Msb:) [my own opinion is most agreeable with this of Ks; and with that of Zj, which will be mentioned below; or, perhaps, is identical with that of Zj: I think it most probable that, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is generally held to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaYN","text_ar":"بَنَىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawN","text_ar":"بَنَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonapN","text_ar":"اِبْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are both originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banayapN","text_ar":"بَنَيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawapN","text_ar":"بَنَوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonapN","text_ar":"اِبْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by suppressing the alif, transferring its kesreh to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", making the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent, and changing the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is therefore said to be not the sign of the fem. gender, either because it is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", but is a substitute for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or because it is preceded by a quiescent letter:] AHn says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for the final radical letter, which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that it is not the sign of the fem. gender, because the letter [next] before it is quiescent: this [he says] is the opinion of Sb, and is the right opinion; for he says that if you were to use it as the proper name of a man, you would make it perfectly decl.; and if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"were to denote the fem. gender, the name would not be perfectly decl.: (TA:) and the same is said respecting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxotN","text_ar":"اُخْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axw","text_ar":"اخو"},{"kind":"text","text":":) this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"remains in a case of pause (Ks, IAar, S, Msb) as in the case of the connexion of the word with a word following: (S:) but one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibinotN","text_ar":"اِبِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, T, S.) because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is required only on account of the quiescence of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is therefore dropped when this is made movent: (S:) Zj says that, in forming the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonapN","text_ar":"اِبْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the sing. is reduced to its original form, which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolapN","text_ar":"فَعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as I find it written in the transcript from the T in the TT, but it may be a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalaPN","text_ar":"فَعَلَپٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with the last radical letter suppressed: (T in TT:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtN","text_ar":"بَنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb) alone: (S:) [and this is generally treated as a fem. pl. of the perfect, or sound, kind, although the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be not a sign of the fem. gender; so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu banaAtika","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ بَنَاتِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw thy daughters;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but sometimes] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu banaAtaka","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ بَنَاتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h [as the case-ending], treating the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a radical letter. (S.) It is said in the Bári' that when men and women are mixed together, the masc. pl. is made predominant; so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw","text_ar":"بَنُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sons and daughters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the children, of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and even,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN mino banY","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ مِنْ بَنى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamiymK","text_ar":"تَمِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman of the children of Temeem"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and accordingly, if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَنُو فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to denote the persons to whom a legacy is left, the males and the females are included therein. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibon","text_ar":"اِبْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to that which is not a human being, (IAmb, Msb,) to an irrational being, (Msb,) it has for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAt","text_ar":"بَنَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAmb, Msb:) thus the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu maxaADK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ مَخَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young male camel in his second year"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu maxaADK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ مَخَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu","text_ar":"اِبْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labuwnK","text_ar":"لَبُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male camel that has entered upon his third year"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu labuwnK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ لَبُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu naEo$K","text_ar":"اِبْنُ نَعْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any one of the stars of the tail of Ursa Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of that of Ursa Minor"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu naEo$K","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ نَعْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but sometimes, by poetic licence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw naEo$K","text_ar":"بَنُو نَعْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence, or to make a distinction between the males and the females, the lawyers say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw All~abuwni","text_ar":"بَنُو اللَّبُونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAmb, Msb.) ―         -b3-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtN","text_ar":"بَنَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dolls with which young girls play:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K:) sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) It occurs in this sense in a trad., in which 'Áïsheh speaks of her playing therewith (S, Mgh) when, being nine years of age, she was conducted as a bride to Mohammad. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibon","text_ar":"اِبْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often prefixed to some other noun (T, M, Msb) that particularizes its signification, because of a close connexion between the two meanings: (Msb:) and so is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binot","text_ar":"بِنْت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, M.) [Most of the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":263},{"kind":"text","text":"compounds thus formed will be found explained in the arts. to which belong the nouns that occupy the second place. The following are among the more common, and are therefore here mentioned, as exs. of different kinds.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu AlT~iyni","text_ar":"اِبْنُ الطِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The son of earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adam."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","Mgh","Msb","M","K","Akh","IAar","TA","Ks","IAmb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}